des:
RCA Smart products help you control home appliance. You can simply ask Alexa to turn on or turn off your light.
There’s no need to go to the switch to adjust your light - just talk to Alexa on your Amazon Echo.
After connecting Alexa to your light in a few simple steps:
(1). Download our "RCA Smart Home" app in android or ios app market;
(2). Register an account in our "RCA Smart Home" app;
(3). You need to have some RCA Smart devices in hand;
(4). Configure these devices in our "RCA Smart Home" app and change appropriate name for your devices which will be used in "RCA Smart Home" skills;
(5). Download Amazon "Alexa" app from android, ios or Amazon app market;
(6). Configure Echo with "Alexa" app;
(7). Search "RCA Smart Home" skill from the "Alexa" app skills category;
(8). Click Enable skill of "RCA Smart Home", and you'll be navigated to "RCA Smart Home" login page;
(9). Input your "RCA Smart Home" account username and password, you'll be redirect to the success page;
(10). Now all setup is finished.

You can enjoy the voice control on your home devices like these:
Alexa, Turn on the light.
Alexa, Turn off the light.
Alexa, Set the light brightness to 25 percent.
Alexa, Set the light brightness to 75 percent.
Alexa, Set the light to warm white.
Alexa, Change light to 4000 kelvin. 
Alexa, Set the light to red.
Alexa, Set the light to blue.
